 is aimed at third year and post-graduate students of politics, public management and health studies. It provides a theoretically inspired account of the development of health policy and organisation in the UK which will also be of interest to academics and researchers in the field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHealth care reformzGreat Britain. 0aMedical policyzGreat Britain. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978186134608740uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781847424211?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847424211423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847424211/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles